nctions in main.rs\n\n| Function | Lines | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `fn main()` | 5703 | Top-level dispatch (entire match cli.command) |\n| `fn noun_table()` | 275 | Verb registry for capture/recall/audit/share (router + help) |\n| `fn render_dashboard()` | 137 | TUI rendering for msg inbox |\n| `fn cmd_migrate_remote()` | 185 | Legacy ref migration |\n| `fn cmd_setup_remote()` | 110 | Git config setup |\n| `fn auto_derive_traces_from_claude_session()` | 93 | Session log parsing |\n| `fn union_merge_trees()` | ~77 | CRDT-style tree merge for context refs |\n| `fn union_merge_notes_commits()` | ~78 | git notes union merge |\n| `fn print_noun_help()` | ~72 | Help printer for verb routing |\n\n### 5. Overall Assessment\n\n**This is a GOD-FILE masquerading as a thin CLI shell.** Here's why:\n\n1. **Bloat:** 10K lines, with `main()` alone being 5.7K lines.\n2. **Mixed concerns:** main.rs contains rendering (TUI), policy enforcement, test orchestration, interactive prompts, noun-verb routing, git config management, and session log parsing — not just dispatch.\n3. **Fragmentation:** 13 separate nested Subcommand enums for what should be flat routing, but the real routing logic (verb remapping) lives in inline code (noun_table, rewrite_noun_argv, maybe_legacy_hint).\n4. **Monolithic match:** 216 match arms in a single function means adding a handler requires scrolling through 5K lines and inserting into the giant match.\n5. **Weak abstraction:** Rendering (render_dashboard, print_doctor_report, print_noun_help) is inline in main.rs; could be extracted to a `ui` module. Noun/verb rewriting (noun_table, rewrite_noun_argv) is entangled CLI logic.\n\n**Recommendation for design review:** Extract:\n- Rendering logic (print_*, render_*) into a `ui/` module\n- Noun/verb system into a `cli/routing.rs` module\n- Interactive prompts (stdin/stdout in Rollback, Msg handlers) into a `cli/interaction.rs` module\n- Each Commands variant handler could move to a separate